# deploy.sh is the authoritative entry point for this sample — it uploads
# every file below directly via the CLI (create scripts, create configs,
# deploy agent, update agentroutines). Listing them here prevents
# `deploy configs` from re-uploading and clobbering what deploy.sh already
# installed (especially the field-guard schema, which deploy.sh attaches
# to the participate routine).
README.md
env.example
.env
deploy.sh
agent.yaml
scripts/
schemas/
examples/
